copy /Y "$(OutDir)$(ProjectName)_d.pdb" "..\..\..\..\..\..\..\stage\"
rem 35-04 (AUDIO-02 gap): refresh the next-to-exe Miles CORE dll. The exe IMPORTS mss32.dll and Windows
rem resolves it from the exe's OWN dir -- a stale next-to-exe core (an older build than the vendored providers)
rem makes AIL_startup crash in mss!RIB_register_interface (provider/core RIB ABI mismatch). Copy the core from
rem the SAME vendored set the providers come from. Unconditional copy /Y = always the matching build, every build.
copy /Y "..\..\..\..\..\..\..\src\external\3rd\library\miles-9.3b\redist\mss32.dll" "..\..\..\..\..\..\..\stage\"
rem 35-03 (AUDIO-02): stage the Miles 9.3b codec redist from the IN-REPO vendored set.
rem Source is the repo-relative src\external\3rd\library\miles-9.3b\redist (Win32 provider set),
rem NOT a machine-specific external install -- a fresh clone stages working audio with no external dependency.
rem Missing miles/ = silent music + in-world-audio loss AND a warning-flood perf drag (UI 2D wavs still play).
rem 9.3b ships NO .m3d providers; the legacy 7.2e .m3d sentinels NEVER exist on a 9.3b stage so they would force a
rem copy every build. Gate on a 9.3b-only provider (mssds3d.flt) to skip redundant copies on a CLEAN stage.
rem NOTE (concern 3): this sentinel CANNOT detect a stale 7.2e stage (7.2e ships mssds3d.flt under the SAME name).
rem The stale-7.2e repair is the explicit Remove-Item stage\miles done before the 35-03 build, NOT this sentinel.
rem xcopy /Y overwrites, so re-running on a populated stage is a safe refresh.
if not exist "..\..\..\..\..\..\..\stage\miles\mssds3d.flt" xcopy /E /I /Y "..\..\..\..\..\..\..\src\external\3rd\library\miles-9.3b\redist" "..\..\..\..\..\..\..\stage\miles\"</Command>
    </PostBuildEvent>
